text: Amelia Dyer (1829 \- 10 June 1896) was an English serial killer, after she was widowed in 1869 she started baby farming. She was executed in 1896 at Newgate Prison. The victim count is often said to be about 400, however likely to be higher, making her one of the most prolific serial killers. ==References== Category:1829 births Category:British serial killers Category:1896 deaths
title: Amelia Dyer
